186DecodeStatus
187FieldParser::ParseFieldsInGeneralPurpose(const std::string &rawInfo, std::string& result)
188{
189 if (rawInfo.empty()) {
190 return DecodeStatus::NoError;
191 }
192
193 auto starts_with =
194 [](const std::string& str, const char* pre) { return strncmp(pre, str.data(), strlen(pre)) == 0; };
195
196 const AiInfo* aiInfo = FindIf(aiInfos, [&](const AiInfo& i) { return starts_with(rawInfo, i.aiPrefix); });
197 if (aiInfo == std::end(aiInfos))
198 return DecodeStatus::NotFound;
199
200 size_t aiSize = AiSize(aiInfo->aiPrefix);
201
202 // require at least one character in the variable field size case
203 if (rawInfo.length() < aiSize + std::max(1, aiInfo->fieldSize))
204 return DecodeStatus::NotFound;
205
206 size_t fieldSize = aiInfo->fieldSize >= 0
207 ? size_t(aiInfo->fieldSize) // fixed
208 : std::min(rawInfo.length() - aiSize, size_t(-aiInfo->fieldSize)); // variable
209
210 auto ai = rawInfo.substr(0, aiSize);
211 auto field = rawInfo.substr(aiSize, fieldSize);
212 auto remaining = rawInfo.substr(aiSize + fieldSize);
213 std::string parsedRemaining;
214 auto status = FieldParser::ParseFieldsInGeneralPurpose(remaining, parsedRemaining);
215 result = '(' + ai + ')' + field + parsedRemaining;
216 return status;
217}
